(18, 0, 4, 1, 53, 5, 'Introduction to Economics Part 1', 'e9616385-361d-11eb-8b83-52540049a927', 'Welcome back! In this segment, we are going to have a recap\r\nof the things we have said so far from the first video to this point. Remember\r\nwe are on the topic, introduction to economics and so far we have looked at the\r\nmeaning of economics, weâ€™ve looked at the various definitions of Economics as\r\noffered by different authorities in Economics.&amp;nbsp;\r\nAnd we have come to the conclusion that the most generally accepted\r\ndefinition among those we have looked at is the one offered by lord Lionel\r\nRobbins which defined economics as the science that studies human behavior as a\r\nrelationship between ends and scarce means which have alternative uses. And we\r\nhave equally pointed out the key concepts in that definition like the concept of\r\nwants which he referred to as ends, the concept of scarcity, the concept of\r\nchoice that is talking about alternative uses.So beyond the definition of Economics, we looked at the\r\nscope of Economics where we said that we are going to constrain ourselves within\r\nthe range of two major branches of economics. i.e the macro and micro aspects\r\nof Economics. So we said that Economics covers both the macro aspect and the\r\nmicro aspect and we said that the micro aspect of Economics deals with the\r\nstudy of individual economic agents or the study of economic units while the\r\nmacro aspect has to do with the study of the economy as a whole i.e the\r\napplication of the various units to study them as one. So the macro aspect of\r\neconomics has to do with those aspects of Economics that have to do with the\r\nwhole economy. Aspects of Economics that have something to do with the whole\r\neconomy like inflation, unemployment, national income and so on and so forth.\r\nSo we went ahead to talk about the importance of economics. And we mentioned\r\nthat economics is very important because it tries to proffer solution to the\r\nproblem of scarcity. So the major reason for the study of economics is to solve\r\nthe problem of scarcity of resources and that is why economics is very\r\nimportant because every human being on the face of the earth faces the problem\r\nof scarcity of resources. And next we talked about the methodology of the study\r\nof economics and we agreed that like any other science subject, Economics uses\r\nthe scientific method to carry out all its investigations. So that is to say,\r\nthat like other scientists, economists apply the scientific method in carrying\r\nout their economic investigations. So take note of that. Economics though it is\r\nsocial science, it uses scientific method in carrying out all its\r\ninvestigations. So after that, we looked at the basic concepts of economics. We\r\nlooked at the concept of wants, the concept of scarcity, the concept of scale\r\nof preference, the concept of choice and finally the concept of opportunity\r\ncost and we mentioned that all of them are very important. There is none that\r\nis more important than the other.&amp;nbsp;So, I thank you very\r\nmuch for following the videos and paying attention and I believe you have\r\nunderstood a lot of things even at this introductory level and have been\r\nmotivated to seek more knowledge on the subject, Economics.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo, I want you to go through the exercise questions provided\r\nand see how much you have appreciated the things we have taught. Try to answer\r\nthe questions on your own and see things foro yourself. See how much of the\r\nthings we have taught you so far youâ€™ve been able to learn. And Iâ€™m very proud\r\nyouâ€™re becoming a better economist even at this introductory level. I believe\r\nyou have been motivated to even make Economics a compulsory subject for\r\nyourself. Iâ€™ll be waiting for you even in the next topic we are going to treat.\r\nThank you!', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RhLsjui2wr8&amp;ab_channel=ACADASUITEEconomics', 'page', '', 1, '', '3f2c7e26-3621-11eb-8b83-52540049a927', '1970-01-01 01:00:00', '1970-01-01 01:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-04 11:09:58', '', 0),
